👉 Multi-Threading

Multiprocessing and Multithreading both are used to achieve multitasking

+-----------+    +-----------+    +-----------+
| Process 1 |    | Process 2 |    | Process 3 |
+-----------+    +-----------+    +-----------+                                
      ⇩                 ⇩                ⇩                                     
      +-----------------+----------------+                                     
                        ⇩                                                      
                    +------+
                    |  OS  |
                    +------+
👉 In a nut shell ...

➜ Threads use shared memory area
➜ Threads => Faster Content Switching
➜ A Thread is light-weight where as a process is heavy weight

For Example : A word processor can have one thread running in foreground as an editor and another in the background auto saving the 
document.

Flow of Control in JAVA :

1. Without Threading :
            +---------+    +---------+    +---------+
            | main()  | ➜ | Func(1) | ➜ | Func(2) | ➜ END     
            +---------+    +---------+    +---------+

2. With Threading :
            +---------+
            | main()  |--------------------------+
            +---------+                          |
                      +---------+                |
                      | Func(1) |----------------+---➜ END
                      +---------+                |
                                +---------+      |
                                | Func(2) |------+
                                +---------+

