👉 Creating a Threads

There are two ways to create a Thread in JAVA

1. By extending Thread Class

Example :

class MyThreads1 extends Thread{
    @Override
    public void run(){
        while (true) {
            System.out.println("My Thread is Running");
            System.out.println("I am Happy");
        }
    }
}
class MyThreads2 extends Thread{
    @Override
    public void run(){
        while (true) {
            System.out.println("My Thread2 is Running");
            System.out.println("I am Sad");
        }
    }
}
public class ThreadsUsingClass {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        MyThreads1 t1 = new MyThreads1();
        MyThreads2 t2 = new MyThreads2();
        t1.start();
        t2.start();
    }
}

Key Take Aways :

1. created 2 threads using class inheritance
2. Each thread overrides run() method
3. start() runs them concurrently
4. Output is continuous and unordered

Output 

My Thread is Running
I am Happy
My Thread2 is Running
I am Sad
My Thread is Running
I am Happy
...
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. By implementing Runnable interface

Example :

class MyThreadRunnable1 implements Runnable{
    public void run () {
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
            System.out.println("I am a Thread1 not a Threat1");
        }
    }
}
class MyThreadRunnable2 implements Runnable{
    public void run () {
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
            System.out.println("I am a Thread2 not a Threat2");
        }
    }
}
public class ThreadsRunnableInterface {
    public static void main() {
        MyThreadRunnable1 bullet1 = new MyThreadRunnable1();
        Thread gun1 = new Thread(bullet1);
        MyThreadRunnable2 bullet2 = new MyThreadRunnable2();
        Thread gun2 = new Thread(bullet2);
        gun1.start();
        gun2.start();
    }
}

Key Take Aways : 

1. Final Summary
2. Runnable → defines task
3. Thread → executes task
4. start() → begins execution
5. Output is parallel + unordered

Output :

I am a Thread1 not a Threat1
I am a Thread2 not a Threat2
I am a Thread2 not a Threat2
I am a Thread2 not a Threat2
I am a Thread2 not a Threat2
I am a Thread1 not a Threat1
I am a Thread1 not a Threat1
I am a Thread1 not a Threat1

Process finished with exit code 0

